      • toString

        public static java.lang.String toString​(java.util.Map map,
                                        char cEntrySep,
                                        char cPairSep)
        From a Map returns a String with following format:
        [key1][pairSep][value1][entrySep][key2][pairsep][value2][entrySep]...[keyN][pairsep][valueN]

        Null keys or values are converted to "null".

        Parameters:
        map - Map to convert into its String representation.
        cEntrySep - Map entry separator
        cPairSep - {Key,Value} pair separator
        Returns:
        A String with above described format.

        public static java.util.Map<java.lang.String,​java.lang.String> toMap​(java.lang.String s,
                                                                           char cEntrySep,
                                                                           char cPairSep)
        Returns a Map of Strings based on format described in map2String method.
        Parameters:
        s - String to convert into a Map.
        cEntrySep - Map entry separator. In "day=22 , month=2" it is the ','
        cPairSep - {Key,Value} pair separator. In "day=22" it is the '='
        Returns:
        The resulting Map.
